rComments: He is very knowledgeable and friendly professor. Small essay every week ranges from 1 to 5 pages depending on the week. Is flexible with extensions. This is a class that I feel teaches you more how to research than learning the actual history. It is an interesting class still. The research topics he gives are interesting and he is an easy grader.
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Lots of homework', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: Professor Moore's class was extremely redundant and I would have avoided it if it wasn't a program requirement. Quite simply the lectures have little impact on the assignments provided in the online format of the class. No tests, just endless papers and meaningless prompts. Finally, he's 1-2 months behind in his marking with the class already over.

Extremely unspecific in instructions and then dings your assignments for lacking specifics. Assigned about 60 total pages of written assignments instead of a midterm and final thinking it would "be easier for us". Takes forever to grade, the course is over now and he hasn't graded anything for over a month.

Took this course online and it was the biggest waste of my time. Weekly papers that had nothing to do with lectures, a question to delve into a famous musicians instagram fro reflection, and he told me that I should have cited my sources to keep academic integrity-for a 1 page assignment. Too lazy to even give us a topic for an 8 page assignment
